@startuml epicd-workitem-state
' epicd — State diagram: a Task's lifecycle across the authoring & execution pipelines.
' FOUR-AXIS model (2026-07-04, proposal §2.3): today's single `state` is decomposed into
'   lane   = pipeline_id (structural)            — which board lane
'   phase  = state (pure progress)               — THIS main diagram
'   turn   = waiting_on ∈ {machine,human,none}   — orthogonal fragment (bottom-left)
'   claim  = Coordinator runtime fact            — legend (queued vs active vs stale)
' `ready`/`in-progress` are MERGED (claim distinguishes queued vs active).
' `needs-human` is NOT a phase — it is waiting_on:=human on whatever phase it happens.

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam state {
  BorderColor #555555
  BackgroundColor #E8F0FE
  BackgroundColor<<gate>> #FFE0B2
  BackgroundColor<<terminal>> #E0E0E0
}

title epicd — Work-item lifecycle (four-axis: phase = state; turn/claim orthogonal)

' ============ PHASE axis (the persisted progress state machine) ============
[*] --> Draft : Human captures\n(kind:feature/chore/epic ; waiting_on=machine)

state "Authoring lane  (pipeline_id = authoring)" as Authoring {
  state Draft
  state Refining
  state Backlog <<gate>>
  Draft --> Refining : scanner claims\n(basic-draft / epic-draft)
  Refining --> Backlog : refine done → **waiting_on:=human**\n(feature→Proposal+Plan / chore→checklist / epic→plan)
  note right of Refining
    Routed by **kind** → RefineStrategy (pure step fn).
    Fine cycle progress (review round N) is strategy-internal,
    surfaced via Coordinator runtime-fact, NOT a phase.
  end note
}

Backlog --> Executing : **Human promote gate**\n(waiting_on:=machine ; authoring→execution)

state "Execution lane  (pipeline_id = execution)" as Execution {
  state chooseRole <<choice>>
  state "Executing\n(ready+in-progress MERGED)" as Executing
  state Decomposing
  state "Awaiting Children" as Awaiting
  state Evaluating

  Executing --> chooseRole : scanner\n(waiting_on=machine ∧ no live claim)
  chooseRole --> Working : role = primitive (Basic)\nfeature→implement / chore→checklist
  chooseRole --> Decomposing : role = compound (Epic)
  state Working
  Decomposing --> Awaiting : creates children\n(role stays compound)
  Awaiting --> Evaluating : all children terminal\n(epic-eval-due)
  note bottom of Working
    claim = live checkout (Coordinator).
    engine.complete() → merge/advance → adjudicate DoD (ENG-8);
    worker may NOT self-write `done`.
  end note
}

state "Done" as Done <<terminal>>

Working --> Done : DoD pass\n(waiting_on:=none)
Working --> Executing : DoD fail → **waiting_on:=human**\n(stays this phase; human decides — see turn fragment)
Evaluating --> Done : epic satisfied\n(waiting_on:=none)
Evaluating --> Executing : epic escalate → **waiting_on:=human**
Done --> [*]

' ============ TURN axis (orthogonal — the ball's court; persisted waiting_on) ============
state "TURN axis · waiting_on (orthogonal to phase)" as Turn {
  state "machine" as T_m
  state "human" as T_h
  state "none" as T_n <<terminal>>
  [*] -> T_m
  T_m --> T_h : gate reached / DoD fail / epic escalate
  T_h --> T_m : Human approves / re-opens (promote or gate-review)
  T_m --> T_n : reaches Done
  T_h --> T_n : Human rejects → archive
}

note bottom of Turn
  **needs-human is HERE, not a phase.** Any phase can hold waiting_on=human
  (promote-gate / gate-review / DoD-fail / epic-escalate all collapse to it).
  monitor picks up ONLY when waiting_on=machine.
end note

note as N_claim
  **CLAIM (runtime, Coordinator) — the 4th axis, not drawn as states:**
  waiting_on=machine ∧ live claim  ⇒ 🤖 active
  waiting_on=machine ∧ no claim     ⇒ ⏳ queued (scanner will pick up)
  waiting_on=machine ∧ claim stale  ⇒ ⚠️ orphaned (was crashed)
  waiting_on=human                   ⇒ 👤 your turn
  Claim (durable+timestamped) IS the checkout record — that is why
  `ready` and `in-progress` need not be separate phases.
end note

note as N_role
  **role** DERIVED from tree (ADR-011 D-1.1): leaf ⇒ primitive (Basic) ·
  has children ⇒ compound (Epic). Decomposing FLIPS primitive→compound.
  role is the TYPE axis — orthogonal to lane(pipeline_id), phase, and turn.
end note

@enduml
